uirements.txt`.\n*   **`setup.py`:** A Python setup script.  It defines how to install the Python package (`zswag`), including its dependencies and entry points.  It is used to package and distribute the Python code.\n\n**`doc/` Directory:**\n\n*   **`zswag-architecture.mdj`:**  A project file for the Visual Paradigm UML modeling tool.  It likely contains a UML diagram representing the architecture of the `zswag` system.\n*   **`zswag-architecture.png`:**  A PNG image representing the architecture diagram of the `zswag` system. This is a visual representation of the system's components and their relationships, probably exported from the `.mdj` file.\n\n**`libs/httpcl/` Directory:**\n\n*   **`CMakeLists.txt`:**  CMake configuration for the `httpcl` library.\n*   **`include/`:**  Contains the header files that define the public interface of the `httpcl` library.\n*   **`src/`:** Contains the source code (.cpp files) implementing the `httpcl` library.\n*   **`test/`:** Contains unit tests for the `httpcl` library.  These tests verify the library's functionality.\n\n**Functionality:** The `httpcl` library appears to be a C++ HTTP client library, responsible for making HTTP requests. This implies it likely handles connection management, request formatting, and response parsing.\n\n**`libs/pyzswagcl/` Directory:**\n\n*   **`CMakeLists.txt`:** CMake configuration for the `pyzswagcl` library.\n*   **`py-openapi-client.cpp`:** C++ source file.  Likely contains the core logic for creating an OpenAPI client.\n*   **`py-openapi-client.h`:** Header file for `py-openapi-client.cpp`.\n*   **`py-zswagcl.cpp`:** C++ source file that acts as the glue between the C++ OpenAPI client library and the Python `zswag` module. It probably uses the Python C API (or a binding library like pybind11) to expose the C++ functionality to Python.\n\n**Functionality:** This library creates a Python extension module. It appears to wrap the C++ OpenAPI client functionality (`py-openapi-client.cpp`) to 